A
The currently effective income tax rate, where FIT is the Federal income tax rate; SIT is the State income tax rate, and p ="the percentage of federal income tax
deductible for state income taxes". If the utility is taxed in more than one state it must attach a work paper showing the name of each state and how the blended
or composite SIT was developed. Furthermore, a utility that elected to utilize amortization of tax credits against taxable income, rather than book tax credits to Account No. 255 and reduce rate base, must reduce its income tax expense by the amount of the Amortized Investment Tax Credit (Form 1, 266.8.f)
multiplied by (1/1-T) (page 3, line 28).
When FIT or SIT statutory tax rate changes take effect on other than a calendar year basis, the statutory rates to be used in the formula rate template shall be
weighted averages for the calendar year determined by weighting the statutory tax rates by the number days each such tax rate was in effect during the calendar year for which the costs are being determined.

p = - (percent of federal income tax deductible for state purposes)
B
Evergy Generating's return calculation is based on the Parent Company. EKS Proprietary Capital is "0" because it is already included in EKC's value. (EKS is a subsidiary of EKC). For Account 216.1, a "0" shall be entered in "Total" if the sum of EKC's and EKS' values is positive.

PURCHASE POWER AGREEMENT BETWEEN EVERGY GENERATING, INC. AND EVERGY KANSAS CENTRAL, INC.
THIS AGREEMENT made as of this 1st day of March, 2013 ("this Agreement:) by and between EVERGY GENERATING, INC., a Kansas corporation ("Evergy Generating"), and EVERGY KANSAS CENTRAL, INC., a public utility incorporated under the laws of the State of Kansas ("Evergy"). WITNESSETH: WHEREAS, Evergy Generating and The Empire District Electric Company ("Empire District") own undivided interests of forty (40) percent and sixty (60) percent, respectively, as tenants in common in the State Line Combined Cycle Generating Facility located in the southwest corner of Jasper County and in Newton County in Missouri (hereinafter referred to as the "SLCC" or the "State Line CC"), which was constructed, owned and operated pursuant to that certain "Agreement for the Construction, Ownership and Operation of State Line Combined Cycle Generating Facility" dated as of July 26, 1999, as it may be amended from time to time (the "State Line CC Agreement"); WHEREAS, Evergy Generating and Evergy previously entered into on February 21, 2001 that certain Gas Purchase Agreement ("Gas Agreement") providing for the delivery and sale by Evergy, and the acceptance and purchase by Evergy Generating, of natural gas; WHEREAS, Evergy entered into a Firm Gas Transportation Agreement with Southern Star Central Gas Pipeline, Inc. on August 12, 2009 and all natural gas that is transported to the State Line CC for use by Evergy will be transported over Transportation Agreement 15140; WHEREAS, the parties desire to provide for Evergy Generating to make available and sell, and for Evergy to accept and purchase Evergy Generating's entire share of the operable capacity and associated energy to be made available from the State Line CC, for a fixed period of time; NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants, representations, warranties and agreements hereinafter set forth, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, and intending to be legally bound hereby, the Parties hereto agree as follows: SECTION 1.
DEFINITIONS Capitalized terms used in this Agreement unless otherwise defined herein shall have the meanings set forth below. 1.1 "Affiliate" means any Person directly or indirectly controlling, controlled by, or under common control with any other Person. The term "control" shall mean the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct the management or policies of a person or an entity. 1.2 "Contract Year" means the twelve consecutive months commencing on July 1 of any year and ending on June 30 of the following year. 1.3 "Energy Delivery Point" means the high voltage bushing of the State Line CC's generator step-up transformers at the point of interconnection with Empire District's transmission system. 1.4 "FERC" means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or any successor agency. 1.5 "Gas Delivery Point" means the point of interconnection between the natural gas inlet facilities located at the State Line CC and the natural gas delivery facilities of the Transportation Provider. 1.6 "Party" or "Parties" means Evergy Generating or Evergy or any permitted successor or assign of Evergy Generating or Evergy. 1.7 "Person" means an individual, corporation, partnership, firm, joint venture association, joint-stock company, trust or unincorporated organization or other legal entity. 1.8 "Proprietary Information" shall have the meaning given in Section 15.1 of this Agreement. 1.9 "Prudent Utility Practice" means, at a particular time, any of the applicable practices, methods and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric utility industry prior to such time, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result when viewed in the context of the overall objectives sought to be obtained with respect to the transactions contemplated by this Agreement, consistent with good business practices, reliability, safety, and expedition. Prudent Utility Practice is not intended to be limited to the optimum practice, method, or act to the exclusion of all others, but rather to a spectrum of practices, methods, or acts having due regard for, among other things, manufacturers' warranties and the requirements of governmental agencies of competent jurisdiction and the requirements of this Agreement and the State Line Documents. 1.10 "State Line Documents" means (i) the State Line CC Agreement and (ii) the Gas Transportation, the Transaction Documents and the Contracts (as each such term is defined in the State Line CC Agreement). 1.11 "Term" means the period defined in Section 13 of this Agreement. 1.12 "Transportation Provider" means Southern Star Central Gas Pipeline. or its successors or assigns providing for the transportation of natural gas to the Gas Delivery Point. 1.13 "Evergy Generating Entitlement" means the amount of capacity (in megawatts) associated with Evergy Generating's forty (40) percent ownership share of the State Line CC and the amount of energy (in megawatt-hours) which Evergy Generating is entitled at the relevant time pursuant to the State Line CC Agreements. SECTION 2.
REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES 2.1 Evergy hereby represents to Evergy Generating as follows: a. Evergy is duly organized, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the jurisdiction of its formation; b. Evergy possesses all requisite power and authority to enter into and perform this Agreement and to carry out the transactions contemplated herein; c. Evergy's execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement have been duly authorized by, or are in accordance with, its organizational documents; this Agreement has been duly executed and delivered in its name on behalf of its duly authorized officers; and this Agreement constitutes the legal, valid, and binding obligation of Evergy, enforceable in accordance with its terms, except as limited by applicable bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or similar laws at the time in effect; d. Evergy's execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement will not result in a breach or violation of, or constitute a default under, any material agreement, lease, or instrument to which it is a party or by which it or any of its properties may be bound or affected; and e. No suit, action, or arbitration, or administrative, legal or other proceeding is pending, or, to Evergy's knowledge, has been threatened against Evergy that would materially affect the validity or enforceability of this Agreement or the ability of Evergy to fulfill its commitments hereunder. 2.2 Evergy Generating hereby represents and warrants to Evergy as follows: a. Evergy Generating is duly organized, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the jurisdiction of its formation; b. Evergy Generating possesses all requisite power and authority to enter into and perform this Agreement and to carry out the transactions contemplated herein; c. Evergy Generating's execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement have been duly authorized by, or are in accordance with, its organizational documents; this Agreement has been duly executed and delivered in its name on behalf of its officers duly authorized; and this Agreement constitutes the legal, valid, and binding obligation of Evergy Generating enforceable in accordance with its terms, except as limited by applicable bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or similar laws at the time in effect. d. Evergy Generating's execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement will not result in a breach or violation of, or constitute a default under, any material agreement, lease, or instrument to which it is a party or by which it or any of its properties may be bound or affected; and e. No suit, action, or arbitration, or administrative, legal or other proceeding is pending or, to Evergy Generating's knowledge, has been threatened against Evergy Generating that would materially affect the validity or enforceability of this Agreement or the ability of Evergy Generating to fulfill its commitments hereunder. SECTION 3.
PURCHASE AND SALE OF UNIT POWER 3.1 Evergy Generating shall accept and purchase from Evergy pursuant to the Gas Agreement all natural gas delivered by Evergy to the Gas Delivery Point. Evergy Generating shall use all natural gas delivered by Evergy for the purpose of generating electric energy from the Evergy Generating Entitlement. Evergy Generating shall not use the natural gas purchased from Evergy for any other purpose and specifically shall not sell the natural gas to any other person, except to any co-owner of the State Line CC as may be contemplated pursuant to the State Line CC Agreement. 3.2 Evergy Generating shall make available and sell and Evergy shall accept and pay for all the capacity and energy (and shall be responsible for the cost of station service) of the Evergy Generating Entitlement, in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. a. Evergy shall have the right to schedule and receive energy at a rate that is: (i) not in excess of that portion of the then maximum operable capacity of the State Line CC to which Evergy Generating is entitled pursuant to the State Line CC Agreement and (ii) not less than that portion of the minimum operable capacity of the State Line CC which Evergy Generating is required to schedule pursuant to the State Line CC Agreement. If Evergy is unwilling or unable to schedule and accept energy at a rate equal to or greater than that portion of the minimum operable capacity of the State Line CC which Evergy Generating is required to schedule, then Evergy shall pay to Evergy Generating the amount charged to Evergy Generating pursuant to the State Line CC Agreement for the costs associated with such unscheduled energy. b. Evergy Generating shall have no obligation to deliver energy to Evergy in excess of the amount of energy produced by natural gas delivered to the Gas Delivery Point by or for the benefit of Evergy. c. The capacity and energy sold hereunder shall be delivered to Evergy at the Energy Delivery Point. Title to and risk of loss for energy and capacity shall pass from Evergy Generating to Evergy at the Energy Delivery Point. 3.3 Evergy Generating hereby appoints and authorizes Evergy to act as Evergy Generating's agent during the term of this Agreement, and Evergy hereby accepts such appointment, to schedule with the Operator (as defined in the State Line CC Agreement) of the State Line CC the delivery of energy associated with the Evergy Generating Entitlement to the Energy Delivery Point and to receive notice from the Operator regarding the removal of the State Line CC from service or the reduction in capacity available to Evergy and other operation and outage data. Evergy shall be responsible for and indemnify Evergy Generating against all costs, charges, liabilities or penalties incurred by Evergy Generating arising from or in any way connected with Evergy's actions as Evergy Generating's agent, including, without limitation, the failure of Evergy to comply with the applicable scheduling procedures of the Operator of the State Line CC or any regional power pool, regional transmission organization or similar entity. 3.4 Subject to the rights and obligations of Evergy Generating under the State Line CC Agreement, Evergy Generating shall use commercially reasonable efforts to cause the operation, maintenance and repair, of the Evergy Generating Entitlement in accordance with applicable law and Prudent Utility Practice in order to make the rated capacity of the Evergy Generating Entitlement, as adjusted for ambient conditions, continuously available to Evergy and maintain rated efficiency. Evergy agrees and acknowledges that Evergy Generating does not operate the State Line CC and that Evergy Generating's rights and obligations with respect to the removal of the State Line CC from operation or the reduction in capacity available to Evergy Generating are subject to the terms and conditions of the State Line CC Agreement. Evergy Generating shall have no liability to Evergy for the removal of the State Line CC from operation or the reduction in capacity of the Evergy Generating Entitlement available to Evergy. The removal of the State Line CC from operation or reduction in capacity available to Evergy Generating shall not affect the monthly Capacity Charge stated in Section 4 of this Agreement. 3.5 If all or part of the Evergy Generating Entitlement is taken out of operation or the capacity available to Evergy is reduced because the State Line CC is partially or totally destroyed or if changes in law or governmental regulation, including but not limited to environmental laws and regulation, requires substantial repairs or changes in equipment to the State Line CC, Evergy Generating shall promptly notify Evergy. The Parties shall then negotiate in good faith to enter into an amendment to this Agreement that restores, to the maximum extent feasible in the circumstances, the benefits and burdens of this Agreement. 3.6 Evergy shall arrange for and be responsible for transportation of natural gas to the Gas Delivery Point. Evergy Generating agrees to provide and Evergy agrees to accept the rights and obligations of Evergy Generating under the Gas Transportation Agreements as defined in the State Line CC Agreement. Evergy shall arrange for and be responsible for all costs associated with the transmission of energy from the Energy Delivery Point. When the State Line CC is out of service, Evergy shall be responsible, at its own expense, for furnishing or arranging for supplying the electrical uses of the State Line CC allocated to Evergy Generating pursuant to the State Line CC Agreement. 3.7 Evergy shall ensure there is natural gas metering equipment at the Gas Delivery Point, as necessary to accurately measure the natural gas receipts. Evergy Generating may request and observe the test of the accuracy of such metering equipment in accordance with the transportation agreement between Evergy and Transportation Provider. 3.8 Evergy Generating shall ensure there is electric metering equipment at the Energy Delivery Point, as necessary to accurately measure deliveries hereunder. 3.9 During the term of this Agreement, Evergy Generating shall not execute or approve any amendment or change to any State Line Document which may adversely affect the rights and obligations of Evergy hereunder, unless Evergy shall have given its prior written consent thereto. Evergy Generating shall give Evergy prior written notice of each such proposed amendment or change and Evergy shall respond as promptly as practicable. 3.10 In exercising its right pursuant to Article IV of the State Line CC Agreement to appoint two representatives to certain committees during the term of this Agreement, Evergy Generating shall appoint one representative designated by Evergy for the purpose of permitting the representative of Evergy to participate in committee meetings and receive communications and committee materials for informational purposes. In any committee action which requires a Supermajority Vote (as defined in and required by the State Line CC Agreement), Evergy Generating shall not take any action (whether in respect of a State Line Document or otherwise) which may have an adverse effect on the rights and obligations of Evergy hereunder unless Evergy shall have given its prior written consent to such action. 3.11 If Evergy Generating shall have been determined, in accordance with the terms and subject to the conditions set forth therein, to be in breach of any obligations under any State Line Document and fails to cure such breach within the required time period, then Evergy may cure such breach on behalf of Evergy Generating and offset the actual direct costs incurred by Evergy in effecting such cure against its obligations to Evergy Generating under Section 4.1(a) hereof. Interest on costs incurred by Evergy or refunded to Evergy Generating shall accrue at the rate established pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 35.19a(a)(2)(iii), as amended. SECTION 4.
CHARGES FOR UNIT POWER 4.1 Evergy shall pay to Evergy Generating the rate based on the application of the formula rate in Appendix A. The formula rate shall be subject to change pursuant to Sections 205 and 206 of the Federal Power Act. 4.2 Evergy shall also pay Evergy Generating the ACA charge, if any, imposed on Evergy Generating by the FERC, provided, however, that Evergy Generating is required to make such payment to FERC under 18 C.F.R. Part 382 et seq., as amended. 4.3 Evergy Generating shall also pay Evergy monthly for the delivered cost of natural gas, as billed and paid pursuant to the Gas Agreement, delivered at the Gas Delivery Point during such month. SECTION 5.
BILLING AND PAYMENT 5.1 Evergy Generating accounting entries are to be processed on a monthly basis recording revenue and fuel expense on Evergy Generating's books and also purchased power expense on Evergy's books related to this contract. All expenses for Evergy Generating are to be paid by Evergy in order to utilize inter-company accounting to record this liability to Evergy. On a quarterly basis, Evergy's controller is to review Evergy Generating's retained earnings balances to determine if it is significant enough to dividend back to Evergy. Evergy Generating's financial information is to be consolidated onto Evergy's books on a monthly basis. 5.2 If Evergy disputes any invoice or payment owing to Evergy Generating, Evergy shall pay Evergy Generating all disputed and undisputed amounts owing. Evergy shall inform Evergy Generating in writing of the detailed reason for such dispute (providing any supporting documentation). If, upon resolution of the dispute, it is determined that Evergy is entitled to reimbursement of any disputed amounts, the reimbursable amount shall include interest calculated in accordance with the methodology specified for interest on refunds in 18 C.F.R. 35.19a(a)(2)(iii), as amended. Such interest will accrue as of the date of payment by Evergy to Evergy Generating of the disputed amount, subject to reimbursement. 5.3 Payments made by Evergy are compensation for electric energy and capacity made available by Evergy Generating. Such payments shall not create ownership or operating rights in Evergy Generating's facilities for Evergy other than the right to schedule energy under this Agreement. SECTION 6. LIMITATION OF REMEDIES, LIABILITY AND DAMAGES 6.1 THE PARTIES CONFIRM THAT THE EXPRESS REMEDIES AND MEASURES OF DAMAGES PROVIDED IN THIS AGREEMENT SATISFY THE ESSENTIAL PURPOSES HEREOF. FOR BREACH OF ANY PROVISION FOR WHICH AN EXPRESS REMEDY OR MEASURE OF DAMAGES IS PROVIDED, SUCH EXPRESS REMEDY OR MEASURE OF DAMAGES SHALL BE THE SOLE AND EXCLUSIVE REMEDY, THE OBLIGOR'S LIABILITY SHALL BE LIMITED AS SET FORTH IN SUCH PROVISION AND ALL OTHER REMEDIES OR DAMAGES AT LAW OR IN EQUITY ARE WAIVED. IF NO REMEDY OR MEASURE OF DAMAGES IS EXPRESSLY HEREIN PROVIDED, THE OBLIGOR'S LIABILITY SHALL BE LIMITED TO DIRECT ACTUAL DAMAGES ONLY, SUCH DIRECT ACTUAL DAMAGES SHALL BE THE SOLE AND EXCLUSIVE REMEDY AND ALL OTHER REMEDIES OR DAMAGES AT LAW OR IN EQUITY ARE WAIVED. UNLESS EXPRESSLY HEREIN PROVIDED, NEITHER PARTY SHALL BE LIABLE FOR CONSEQUENTIAL, INCIDENTAL, PUNITIVE, EXEMPLARY OR INDIRECT DAMAGES, LOST PROFITS OR OTHER BUSINESS INTERRUPTION DAMAGES (INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE PURCHASE OF REPLACEMENT POWER), BY STATUTE, IN TORT OR CONTRACT, UNDER ANY INDEMNITY PROVISION OR OTHERWISE. IT IS THE INTENT OF THE PARTIES THAT THE LIMITATIONS HEREIN IMPOSED ON REMEDIES AND THE MEASURE OF DAMAGES BE WITHOUT REGARD TO THE CAUSE OR CAUSES RELATED THERETO, INCLUDING THE NEGLIGENCE OF ANY PARTY, WHETHER SUCH NEGLIGENCE BE SOLE, JOINT OR CONCURRENT, OR ACTIVE OR PASSIVE. TO THE EXTENT ANY DAMAGES REQUIRED TO BE PAID HEREUNDER ARE LIQUIDATED, THE PARTIES ACKNOWLEDGE THAT THE DAMAGES ARE DIFFICULT OR IMPOSSIBLE TO DETERMINE, OTHERWISE OBTAINING AN ADEQUATE REMEDY IS INCONVENIENT AND THE LIQUIDATED DAMAGES CONSTITUTE A REASONABLE APPROXIMATION OF THE HARM OR LOSS. THE PROVISIONS OF THIS SECTION 6.1 SHALL SURVIVE THE TERMINATION OR EXPIRATION OF THIS AGREEMENT. 6.2 Nothing in this Agreement shall be construed to create any duty, standard of care or liability to any Person not a Party to this Agreement. SECTION 7.
INDEMNITY Subject to Section 9.2 hereof, each Party expressly agrees to indemnify, hold harmless and defend the other Party, its officers, directors, employees, agents its Affiliates and their officers, directors, employees and agents from and against any and all losses, claims, damages or liabilities to third parties (including, without limitation, reasonable fees, disbursements and expenses for attorneys and experts) for personal injury, death or property damage to third parties caused by the gross negligence or willful misconduct of the indemnifying Party relating to the capacity and energy to be delivered or received, as the case may be, under this Agreement while title is held by the indemnifying Party, except to the extent such injury, death or property damage is attributable to the gross negligence or willful misconduct of the Party seeking indemnification hereunder or its officers, directors, employees, or agents. The indemnified Party shall promptly notify the indemnifying Party in writing of any such claim or suit and the indemnifying Party shall be permitted, upon accepting financial responsibility, to control a defense against or settlement (other than any defense or settlement involving criminal liability or admission of guilt or responsibility by the indemnified Party or its officers, directors, employees, agents or Affiliates) of such claim or suit through counsel of its choice. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the obligations of the indemnifying Party are conditioned upon the indemnified party providing such cooperation as the indemnifying Party may reasonably request in connection with its defense or settlement of the claim or suit against the indemnified Party. SECTION 8.
UNCONTROLLABLE FORCES 8.1 The term "Uncontrollable Forces" as used herein (i) shall mean causes not within the control of the Party directly affected and claiming suspension of its obligations (other than the payment of monetary obligations) and which by the exercise of due diligence and foresight could not reasonably have been avoided, and (ii) shall be deemed to include, but not be limited to, acts of God, acts of civil or military authorities, acts of war or public enemy, acts of any court, regulatory agency or administrative body having jurisdiction, insurrections, riots, strikes or other labor disturbances, breakdown of or accidents to plant, equipment or facilities, fires, explosions, floods, drought or similar acts of nature, interruption of transportation, embargoes or other causes of a similar nature; provided that any strike or other labor disturbance may be settled at the sole discretion of the Party directly affected thereby. 8.2 If Uncontrollable Forces prevent a Party from performing, in whole or in part, any of its obligations under this Agreement, other than the obligations to make payments hereunder (unless the means of transferring funds is affected), shall be suspended and the Party shall not be considered to be in default in respect to such obligation; provided, that the suspension of the Party's obligations is of no greater scope and of no longer duration than is required by the Uncontrollable Forces. A Party unable to fulfill any obligation under this Agreement by reason of Uncontrollable Forces shall exercise due diligence to remove such disability, if practicable, with reasonable dispatch using commercially reasonable efforts, except that any labor disturbance may be settled at the discretion of the Party affected thereby. 8.3 The Party invoking Uncontrollable Forces shall provide the other Party with prompt notice thereof. When an event of Uncontrollable Forces ceases, the Party relying thereon shall give prompt notice thereof to the other Party. Notices given by telephone shall be confirmed in writing as soon as reasonably possible. Regardless of the suspension of either Party's obligations by reason of Uncontrollable Forces, this Agreement shall terminate as of the end of the Term. SECTION 9.
DEFAULT, TERMINATION AND REMEDIES 9.1 The occurrence of one or more of the following events so long as the same is continuing shall constitute an "Event of Default" under this Agreement: a. the failure by either Party to pay any amount due under this Agreement which continues for a period of ten (10) days after receipt of notice of such non-payment by such Party from the other Party; and b. the failure by either Party to substantially perform any other material obligation under this Agreement for which a remedy is not expressly provided hereunder, and which failure continues for a period of thirty (30) days after notice thereof has been received by such Party from the other Party. 9.2 This Agreement may be terminated by the non-defaulting Party if the defaulting Party fails to cure the Event of Default within the cure periods provided under Section 9.1 and the defaulting Party has not resolved the dispute by any other means mutually agreed upon by the Parties with respect to the alleged Event of Default. Upon termination, the non-defaulting Party shall be entitled to such damages as are available at law and equity, except that neither Party shall be liable for any indirect, punitive, treble, special or consequential damages by reason of an Event of Default under this Agreement. The termination of this Agreement under this Section 9.2 shall not discharge either Party from any obligations which may have accrued under this Agreement prior to such termination. The Parties hereto recognize and acknowledge that Evergy Generating is not the operator of State Line CC and, consequently, hereby agree that Evergy Generating shall have no liability to Evergy for any claim arising out of the operation of State Line CC or the delivery of the output therefrom. If requested by Evergy, Evergy Generating agrees to make a claim against the operator of State Line CC for any claim that Evergy may have arising out of the operation of State Line CC or the delivery of the output therefrom; provided, that (i) Evergy shall indemnify and promptly reimburse Evergy Generating (on an as-incurred basis) for any and all costs, expenses or liabilities suffered by Evergy Generating in connection with any such claim against the operator of State Line CC; and (ii) Evergy Generating shall not be required to bring any claim against the operator of State Line CC to the extent that Evergy Generating is advised by counsel that such claim is either without merit or does not stand a reasonable likelihood of success. To the extent permitted by the State Line CC Agreements, Evergy may elect to bring a claim against the operator of the State Line CC directly rather than through Evergy Generating in the manner discussed in this Section 9.2. In the event that Evergy elects to bring a claim directly, Evergy Generating shall be relieved of any obligation under this Section 9.2 with respect to such claim. SECTION 10.
WAIVERS Any waiver at any time by either party of its rights with respect to a default under this Agreement, or with respect to any other matter arising in connection with this Agreement, shall not be deemed a waiver with respect to any subsequent default or matter. Any delay short of the statutory period of limitation in asserting or enforcing any right shall not be deemed a waiver of such right. SECTION 11.
AUDIT RIGHTS Either party, or its representatives, shall have the right, at its sole expense and during normal working hours, to examine the applicable books, records and underlying source documentation to verify the accuracy of any statement or computation made pursuant to this Agreement. Such examinations shall be scheduled during normal business hours. If any such examination reveals any inaccuracy in any statement, the necessary adjustments in such statements and payments thereof will be promptly made. Interest on any unpaid amount shall be calculated in accordance with the methodology specified for interest on refunds in the FERC's regulations at 18 C.F.R. 35.19a(a)(2)(iii), as amended, and shall bear interest calculated at such rate from the date the overpayment or underpayment was made until paid. The Parties' rights and obligations under this Section shall survive any termination of this Agreement for a period of two years from the date of such termination for the purpose of statement and payment objections. Evergy Generating shall have no obligation under this Agreement to retain any records beyond the period specified in 18 C.F.R. Part 125 for purposes of auditing or adjusting statements or payments. SECTION 12.
REGULATORY APPROVAL 12.1 The Parties recognize that this Agreement is subject to the jurisdiction of FERC and that Evergy Generating will file this Agreement with FERC. The Parties agree to use commercially reasonable efforts to seek and obtain FERC's prompt approval of this Agreement. 12.2 If the FERC issues an order not accepting this Agreement for filing in its entirety or without material change, then the parties shall amend this Agreement to conform to the requirements of such order. 12.3 The Parties agree that the provisions of this Agreement, including without limitation the rates and charges and conditions of the service contained herein, are subject to change by FERC, and that Evergy Generating and Evergy shall be entitled, at any time and from time to time, unilaterally and in the sole discretion of each, to apply for or to take other action to request such a change under Sections 205 or 206 of the Federal Power Act ("FPA"), respectively, and pursuant to the rules and regulations promulgated thereunder (Sections 205 or 206) or any other change that is required or allowed by any legal, regulatory, statutory, or other governing authority. The standard of review FERC shall apply when acting on such proposed changes shall be the "just and reasonable" standard of review rather than the "public interest" standard of review set forth in United Gas Pipe Line Co. v. Mobile Gas Services Corp., 350 U.S. 332 (1956) and Federal Power Commission v. Sierra Pacific Power Co., 350 U.S. 348 (1956) (the Mobile-Sierra Doctrine). SECTION 13.
TERM 13.1 This Agreement shall become effective July 1, 2013 and shall continue in full force and effect from the effective date until the conclusion of the fifth Contract Year and then remain in effect from year-to-year, unless earlier terminated on 12 months prior written notice or in accordance with other provisions of this Agreement, and shall remain in effect after termination only to the extent necessary to provide for final billings and adjustments and to give effect to a Party's surviving rights and remedies hereunder. SECTION 14.
ASSIGNMENT AND PURCHASE OPTION 14.1 Neither Party shall transfer or assign this Agreement or its rights, title and interest hereunder without the prior written consent of the other Party, said consent not to be unreasonably withheld; provided, however, that (i) either Party may, without the consent of the other Party (and without relieving itself from liability hereunder), transfer, sell, pledge, encumber or assign this Agreement or the accounts, revenues or proceeds hereof in connection with any financing or other financial arrangements, (ii) either Party may transfer or assign this Agreement to an Affiliate of such Party, (iii) Evergy Generating may transfer or assign this Agreement in part or in its entirety to any Person succeeding to all or a portion of the Evergy Generating Entitlement and (iv) Evergy may transfer or assign this Agreement to any Person succeeding to all or substantially all of the assets of Evergy. No assignment or disposition pursuant to this Section 14 shall relieve or in any way discharge the assigning Party from the performance of its duties and obligations under this Agreement, unless and until the assigning Party has delivered to the other Party a duly executed assignment and assumption agreement in which the assignee unconditionally assumes all of the assigning Party's obligations and duties under this Agreement. For purposes of this Section 14, the term "Evergy Generating Entitlement" shall mean and include Evergy Generating's interests as an "Owner" under and in respect of the State Line Documents. 14.2 If, at any time during the useful life of the State Line CC, Evergy Generating or Parent (as defined below) desires to dispose of its right, title or interest in all or a portion of the Evergy Generating Entitlement (including by means of the sale of stock, indirect transfer of ownership interests, lease, or power sale agreement with a term equal to or greater than three years), or receives an offer from any other Person to acquire by any such means (a "Transfer") all or a portion of the Evergy Generating Entitlement which Evergy Generating is prepared to accept, then Evergy Generating shall give notice thereof in writing to Evergy (a "Transfer Notice"). The Transfer Notice shall specify the terms under which Evergy Generating is prepared to transfer its interest in the Evergy Generating Entitlement, including the purchase price and/or other terms and conditions and the closing date, or include a copy of the offer received from offeror, as the case may be. Upon receipt of a Transfer Notice, Evergy shall have a period of thirty (30) days in which to exercise its option to acquire the Evergy Generating Entitlement by giving written notice thereof to Evergy Generating (an "Offer Notice"). If Evergy timely elects to exercise its option, Evergy shall be entitled to acquire the Evergy Generating Entitlement on the same non-price terms and conditions stated in the Transfer Notice and, in the case of a Transfer which is a sale, at a price equal to the lesser of (i) the price stated in the Transfer Notice and (ii) one hundred twenty percent (120%) of the depreciated net book value of the Evergy Generating Entitlement (or portion thereof) at that time. In the case of a Transfer by any other means, Evergy shall be entitled to acquire the Evergy Generating Entitlement on the same non-price terms and conditions stated in the Transfer Notice and at price terms equal to the lesser of (i) the price terms stated in the Transfer Notice and (ii) the price terms which equate to a fair consideration based on an assumed value of the portion of the Evergy Generating Entitlement in question equal to one hundred twenty percent (120%) of its then depreciated net book value (such assumed to take into account the terms and provisions of this Section 14.2). If (i) Evergy fails to exercise its option within such thirty (30) day option period, or (ii) Evergy timely exercises its option and the transaction between Evergy and Evergy Generating fails to close within two hundred seventy (270) days after the expiration of the thirty (30) day option period, then Evergy Generating may transfer the Evergy Generating Entitlement to any Person on any terms and conditions and at any price acceptable to Evergy Generating. Evergy shall not have a right of first refusal for any disposition of the Evergy Generating Entitlement made in connection with any financing transaction or, if Evergy has assigned its rights and obligations under the Agreement to a non-Affiliate, to an Affiliate of Evergy Generating. SECTION 15.
PROPRIETARY INFORMATION 15.1 Evergy Generating and Evergy may find it necessary to exchange information of a proprietary and confidential nature, including, but not limited to cost data and other commercially sensitive information. The Parties agree to maintain in confidence all information received from one Party (the "Transmitting Party") by the other Party (the "Receiving Party") which is designated in writing as proprietary or confidential ("Proprietary Information"). Proprietary Information shall not include (a) information which has at the relevant time entered the public domain other than by reason of breach of this provision by the Receiving Party, (b) information derived by the Receiving Party from sources other than the Transmitting Party and not as a result of a breach of this Agreement, (c) information required to be disclosed pursuant to Section 15.3, and (d) information known to the Receiving Party prior to receipt of such information from the Transmitting Party. 15.2 The Receiving Party shall use such Proprietary Information exclusively in connection with the purchase and sale of energy and capacity from the State Line CC. The Receiving Party shall not transmit or disclose such Proprietary Information to any Person, without first obtaining the prior written approval of the Transmitting Party. This restriction shall not apply to the disclosure of Proprietary Information by the Receiving Party to those of its employees, agents, attorneys and accountants having a need for such information, provided such Party uses its reasonable efforts to cause such recipients to maintain the information in strict confidence. 15.3 When required by law or by any order rule or regulation (whether valid or invalid) of any court or governmental authority, the Receiving Party may disclose Proprietary Information to the extent required; provided, that prior to making any such disclosure, the Receiving Party shall: (a) provide the Transmitting Party with timely advance notice of the Receiving Party's intent to so disclose Proprietary Information; (b) minimize the amount of Proprietary Information to be provided consonant with the interests of the Transmitting Party and the requirements of the governmental authority involved; and (c) make reasonable efforts to cooperate with the Transmitting Party in attempting to secure confidential treatment for Proprietary Information to the extent feasible. In the event that efforts to secure confidential treatment are unsuccessful, the Transmitting Party shall have the prior right to revise such information to minimize the disclosure of such information in a manner consonant with its interests and the requirements of the governmental authority involved. 15.4 Upon the termination of this Agreement, each Party shall promptly return or destroy Proprietary Information received from the other Party and any copies made of such information. The Receiving Party's confidentiality obligations under this Section 15 shall expire two (2) years from the date it receives such Proprietary Information hereunder, or such longer period as agreed to by the Parties prior to disclosure to the other Party. SECTION 16.
MISCELLANEOUS 16.1 This Agreement and the Schedules hereto constitute the entire agreement between the Parties. There are no prior or contemporaneous agreements or representations affecting the same subject matter other than those herein expressed. Except for any matters which, in accordance with the express provisions of this Agreement, may be resolved by verbal agreement between the Parties and for changes authorized by the FERC under Section 205 or 206 of the Federal Power Act, as amended, no modification, amendment or change herein shall be enforceable unless reduced to writing and executed by the Parties. This Agreement and all of the provisions hereof shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the parties hereto and their respective successors and permitted assigns. 16.2 This Agreement shall be governed by, and construed and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the State of Kansas (regardless of the laws that might otherwise govern under applicable Kansas principles of conflicts of laws). 16.3 All notices shall be in writing signed by a duly authorized representative of the Party giving such notice and shall be transmitted in person, by registered mail, certified mail, express courier, or telefax (followed by registered or certified mail or express courier) to the other Party at the designated address below: a. Either Party shall have the right to change the place to which such notice shall be sent or delivered by similar notice sent in like manner to the other Party. 16.4 Notices delivered to a Party under this Agreement shall become effective upon such Party's receipt of such notice. Receipt shall be conclusively presumed to have occurred when delivery is made by: (i) personal service upon the Party to be given such notice that the addressed designated above; (ii) telephone facsimile transmission provided that the recipient acknowledges that it has received such notice; (iii) a courier or other delivery service, provided that the recipient or its agent signs a receipt acknowledging receipt from the courier or delivery service; (iv) three (3) business days after it has been deposited in the United States Mail, properly addressed, certified or registered with a return receipt requested and with postage thereon fully prepaid. 16.5 Unless the context otherwise requires: a term has the meaning assigned to it in this Agreement; "including" means including, without limitation; "or" is not exclusive; words in the singular include the plural and words in the plural include the singular; and references to sections, articles and schedules of and to this Agreement unless otherwise expressly indicated, and references to the provisions "herein" or "hereof" and other similar references refer to this Agreement in its entirety. 16.6 This Agreement may be executed by the parties hereto in separate counterparts, each of which when so executed and delivered shall be an original, but all such counterparts shall together constitute but one and the same instrument. 16.7 The Table of Contents and headings of the various Sections of this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. 16.8 This Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the Parties hereto and their respective successors and assigns.
